{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-13","name":"Lord Otterus Othoer di Gherardini","nameForms":[{"lang":"und","fullText":"Lord Otterus Othoer di Gherardini","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Prefix","value":"Lord"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Otterus Othoer"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"di Gherardini"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"0934–0996","fullLifespan":"0934–0996","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/0ou2l/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"DOCUMENT","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-93430-4060-32/dist.pdf?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/94675297","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-93430-4060-32/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"The Garretts -- Before America","description":"The Garretts — Before America\nby John E. Garrett\nLast year, I published my work entitled, \"1000 Years of Garrett Family History\". The emphasis in that effort\nwas the genealogy of the Garretts since their immigration to America in the mid-seventeenth century. This\nwork examines how the Garretts evolved during the generations that they spent in England, Wales and\nIreland from the time the first ancestor landed in England until the first Garrett came to America.\nMy research involved the use of:\n A commercial genealogy website named Ancestry.com.\n Extensive use of the Google search engine on the Internet\nThe first 100 years, starting in the eleventh century, was the most interesting. That was where I found a\nremarkable relationship between my ancestors and King Edward the Confessor, King William the Conqueror\nand King Henry I. My first ancestor to land in England, Otho Geraldini, grew-up with Edward before he\nbecame King; his son Walter FitzOtho was in William, the Bastard's army; and his son Gerald grew-up with\nPrince Henry (King William\"s son) who became King Henry I. Their close relationship is demonstrated by the\nvast amount of land, castles and titles bestowed upon them.\nIn retrospect, I am impressed at how important the genes of the spouses are to the family's genealogy. The\nbest example of this is when my ancestor, Gerald of Windsor married Nesta Rhys, a Welsh Princess. There\noffsprings were all outstanding. The next \"high\" came when the Garrett's became merchants in the 16th\ncentury, opened trade with Russia, became Lord Mayor of London and honorary knighthood.\nTo make this work more readable, I have placed several interesting \"asides\" in the Appendix. For example,\nthe de Clares, of Richard \"Strongbow\" de Clare fame married into the Garretts. I found extensive genealogy\non the ancestry of Richard \"Strongbow\" de Clare going back before 100 AD. So, I put his data into two\nappendices. One for the French ancestors and another for the Viking ancestors. ","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-76811-303-73/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/43510332","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-76811-303-73/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-904-76811-303-73/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-88084-3818-48/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/77267184","headline":"Otterus ","description":"* BIOGRAPHY: Otterus was \" an Italian Baron of the Gherardini of Florence, Lord in Tuscany \" and went from Florence into Normandy, then to England and Wales about 11